   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Mixing long-term and short-term optimization targets\n",
    "\n",
    "In energy, we typically face very short-term optimization tasks (e.g. 15min intervals in power) as well as long-term effects such as saisonality. Bringing both together in optimization can easily make complexity explode -- if we optimize all assets on the most granular time grid. In our approach we allow all assets bring along their own time-scale, which may be different from the time-scale that is used on portfolio level.\n",
    "\n",
    "In this example we explain the feature using a rather simple example:\n",
    "* power market with hourly prices that exhibit an hourly as well as a seasonal structure\n",
    "* a short-term storage such as a smaller pump storage or a battery that is optimized hourly on a daily basis - but not across more than a week\n",
    "* a long-term storage such as a high-volume hydro reservoir that is optimized across the whole seaon on a biweekly basis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Some prerequisites\n",
    "### Basics"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import datetime as dt\n",
    "# in case eao is not installed\n",
    "import os\n",
    "import sys\n",
    "# in case eao is not installed, set path\n",
    "myDir = os.path.join(os.getcwd(), '../..')\n",
    "sys.path.append(myDir)\n",
    "addDir = os.path.join(os.getcwd(), '../../../..')\n",
    "sys.path.append(addDir)\n",
    "\n",
    "import eaopack as eao\n",
    "\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "%matplotlib inline"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Define portfolio\n",
    "\n",
    "We use three different assets:\n",
    "* Market: a simple contract with a given market price\n",
    "* Short-term storage, acting on an hourly basis. We reduce the complexity by enforcing that the optimization is done for every day, but not across weeks\n",
    "* Long-term storage acting on a weekly level for the whole season: We reduce complexity by assuming the same (here flat) profile for all hours within two weeks\n",
    "\n",
    "Note: For sake of clarity in the charts we do the optimization on daily granularity. Finer overall granularity (e.g. hours) is defined on portfolio level in the timegrid\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "start = dt.date(2021,1,1)\n",
    "end   = dt.date(2021,12,31)\n",
    "\n",
    "# the basic setup\n",
    "node = eao.assets.Node('node')\n",
    "timegrid = eao.assets.Timegrid(start, end, freq = 'd')\n",
    "market = eao.assets.SimpleContract(name = 'market', price = 'price', nodes = node ,\n",
    "                min_cap= -1000., max_cap=1000., start = start, end = end)\n",
    "# daily flex\n",
    "st = eao.assets.Storage('ST storage', nodes = node, \\\n",
    "        start=start, end=end, size=10, \\\n",
    "        cap_in=2/24, cap_out=2/24, start_level=5, end_level=5, \\\n",
    "        block_size= 'W')\n",
    "# weekly flex\n",
    "lt = eao.assets.Storage('LT storage', nodes = node, \\\n",
    "        start=start, end=end, size=500, \\\n",
    "        cap_in=2/24, cap_out=2/24, start_level=100, end_level=100, \\\n",
    "        freq = '14d')\n",
    "\n",
    "# price with seasonal and daily pattern\n",
    "prices ={'price': 10*np.sin(np.linspace(0,2*np.pi, timegrid.T)) \\\n",
    "                + 2*np.sin(np.linspace(0,7*12*np.pi, timegrid.T)) \\\n",
    "                + 2*np.sin(np.linspace(0,7**24*2*np.pi, timegrid.T))}\n",
    "\n",
    "portf = eao.portfolio.Portfolio([market, st, lt])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The below network chart shows the setup of the portfolio. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "eao.network_graphs.create_graph(portf = portf, title = 'Simple portfolio example')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Perform the optimization"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "op    = portf.setup_optim_problem(prices, timegrid)\n",
    "res = op.optimize()\n",
    "out = eao.io.extract_output(portf, op, res, prices)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Create charts and interpret the results"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 864x288 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1,2, tight_layout = True, figsize=(12,4))\n",
    "out['dispatch'][['ST storage', 'LT storage']].plot(ax = ax[0], style = '-')\n",
    "out['prices']['input price: price'].plot(ax = ax[1], style = '-')\n",
    "ax[0].set_title('power')\n",
    "ax[1].set_title('power price')\n",
    "plt.show()\n"
   ]
  }
 ],
